The paper discusses reputation mechanisms in electronic markets, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). It also deals with issues of trust and security, which are relevant to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of feedback and incentives to promote honest reporting suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on the establishment of reputation and the prevention of false reports could be relevant to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
